DIGEST
SB 332 Original 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Present law prohibits the knowing and intentional disposal in a landfill of waste tires that are
not subjected to processing or recycling. Provides that tires prepared by cutting, separating,
shredding, or other means may be disposed of in a landfill.
Proposed law retains present law and provides that whole tires that have not been prepared
by cutting, separating, shredding, or other means may not be disposed of in a landfill.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 30:2418(C))
